WEBVTT

00:00.849 --> 00:02.349
<i>Previously on</i> Blue Bloods:

00:03.695 --> 00:05.563
What's going on, kid?

00:09.852 --> 00:11.986
Something you should hear.

00:11.987 --> 00:13.855
JOE
Getting close,

00:13.856 --> 00:16.658
but the Templar
may have made me.

00:16.659 --> 00:17.726
That's Joe.

00:17.727 --> 00:19.060
The night he
was killed.

00:19.061 --> 00:23.364
He was working with the FBI,
investigating the Blue Templar.

00:23.365 --> 00:25.333
What?

00:25.334 --> 00:28.203
I should have told you
a long time ago, Danny.

00:28.204 --> 00:30.205
Does Dad know?

00:30.206 --> 00:32.540
No.

00:40.883 --> 00:44.185
After I broke off
communications with the FBI,

00:44.186 --> 00:45.553
I started looking into the death

00:45.554 --> 00:47.288
of Detective Gonsalves
on my own.

00:47.289 --> 00:48.690
Long story short, she had left

00:48.691 --> 00:52.160
a sort of last testament
with her sister.

00:52.161 --> 00:54.362
Wrote that when she
arrived on the scene,

00:54.363 --> 00:56.965
Detective Malevsky
had killed the two dealers

00:56.966 --> 00:59.701
and then told her
that they had shot Joe.

01:05.241 --> 01:07.275
She didn't believe him,

01:07.276 --> 01:08.676
so the Blue Templar realized

01:08.677 --> 01:10.612
that, clearly,
that made her a liability.

01:12.381 --> 01:15.216
Why didn't you come to us
when all this started?

01:16.252 --> 01:19.220
Because Joe had kept it
from you, I...

01:20.856 --> 01:22.190
...thought maybe
this was something

01:22.191 --> 01:24.025
he left behind
for me to...

01:24.026 --> 01:27.028
carry on, and...

01:29.915 --> 01:32.267
I wanted to honor my brother.

01:38.440 --> 01:40.241
Now I'm in over my head.

01:40.242 --> 01:42.744
I mean, uh...

01:42.745 --> 01:45.613
who the hell are these guys?

01:53.722 --> 01:55.924
We're going in the front.

01:57.426 --> 02:00.595
Copy that.
We're at the fire escape.

02:03.866 --> 02:07.435
After Serpico
and the Knapp Commission

02:07.436 --> 02:10.038
and all the static
that came with it,

02:10.038 --> 02:13.508
we started the Blue Templar as
a way to police the police.

02:13.509 --> 02:16.477
There was a world of hurt
in the ranks

02:16.478 --> 02:18.413
because a few bad apples had...

02:18.414 --> 02:20.415
brought such disgrace
to the whole department.

02:20.416 --> 02:23.184
We thought it would be
a good thing

02:23.185 --> 02:25.186
to have a band of brothers

02:25.187 --> 02:27.789
who kept a lookout
from the inside.

02:29.258 --> 02:31.960
And it served a purpose
for awhile.

02:31.961 --> 02:34.462
We had a good man in I.A.

02:34.463 --> 02:37.165
who appreciated
what we were trying to do.

02:37.166 --> 02:40.001
And we avoided
some potential disasters

02:40.002 --> 02:42.003
from the rank.

02:42.004 --> 02:46.474
But after a while, the...
the core group retired,

02:46.475 --> 02:48.476
and the Templar became

02:48.477 --> 02:50.945
just a bunch of guys
telling war stories

02:50.946 --> 02:53.481
about the bad old days.

02:55.851 --> 02:58.653
I was never much of a joiner.

02:58.654 --> 03:02.123
When I was tapped, there was
some new blood in the Templar.

03:02.124 --> 03:04.959
Thought we could do
some good again.

03:04.960 --> 03:07.295
Just dissolved into
a bunch of blowhards

03:07.296 --> 03:09.030
sitting around
strip clubs

03:09.031 --> 03:10.598
where the girls
know every cop's name

03:10.599 --> 03:13.201
and a bill never shows up
for the drinks.

03:13.202 --> 03:15.403
I got out quick.

03:17.556 --> 03:18.890
Police! Don't move!

03:20.000 --> 03:26.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:30.452 --> 03:32.820
Come on, come on, come on.

03:35.524 --> 03:37.725
When I came on
as commissioner,

03:37.726 --> 03:41.262
I conducted a thorough review
of all the department's

03:41.263 --> 03:43.498
fraternal organizations
with I.A.,

03:43.499 --> 03:47.068
including the Blue Templar.

03:47.069 --> 03:51.773
I never saw anything
that would cause concern,

03:51.774 --> 03:54.342
much less alarm.

03:56.645 --> 04:00.148
I guess I just saw
what I was supposed to see.

04:07.723 --> 04:10.525
Who was your FBI contact?

04:10.526 --> 04:12.860
A female agent--
Anderson.

04:12.861 --> 04:15.663
She just made it sound like
Joe was working with them.

04:15.664 --> 04:17.265
Anybody else? I.A.?

04:17.266 --> 04:19.100
Lieutenant Bello
interviewed me from I.A.

04:19.101 --> 04:21.269
when I was seen in Chinatown
with Anderson.

04:21.269 --> 04:24.605
She came forward and...
and backed up my... my story.

04:30.346 --> 04:32.213
You lied to I.A.

04:34.817 --> 04:38.252
I didn't know
who knew what. I...

04:39.388 --> 04:42.457
You should have come to me
right away, son.

04:51.400 --> 04:52.934
Yeah.

04:53.769 --> 04:55.503
No, you go ahead.

04:55.504 --> 04:57.238
I'll meet you there.

05:12.554 --> 05:13.638
Hey. What do we got?

05:13.639 --> 05:15.556
Hey. Uh, well, all
four were packing.

05:15.557 --> 05:17.141
None of them
got off a shot.

05:17.142 --> 05:19.594
We got two earwitnesses
that heard some commotion

05:19.595 --> 05:22.797
and then a lot of gunfire
in a short amount of time.

05:22.798 --> 05:24.098
We gathering the shell casings?

05:24.099 --> 05:25.299
Yeah, but both witnesses said

05:25.300 --> 05:26.801
they heard
voices-- plural--

05:26.802 --> 05:29.270
shouting what sounds like,
"Police. Don't move."

05:29.271 --> 05:30.971
Right.
"Police. Don't move,"

05:30.972 --> 05:32.907
but nobody stops
to take a peek, right?

05:32.908 --> 05:34.492
Right, well, in a
building like this,

05:34.493 --> 05:35.643
"Police. Don't move..."

05:35.644 --> 05:38.179
Even the cockroaches
run the other way.

05:39.014 --> 05:41.382
Hey.

05:42.251 --> 05:44.619
Hey.

05:46.522 --> 05:49.357
Hey, look wedged in right there.

05:50.492 --> 05:52.527
See it?

05:52.528 --> 05:54.462
Is that Kevlar?

05:54.463 --> 05:56.664
Yeah, looks like it.

05:59.601 --> 06:02.370
That's a Kevlar glove,
same as the police use.

06:02.371 --> 06:03.571
They're shouting
police commands.

06:03.572 --> 06:04.972
Right. Police
impersonators?

06:04.973 --> 06:06.307
Yeah.

06:06.308 --> 06:08.376
Or maybe, uh, dirty cops.

06:08.377 --> 06:10.778
We had an incident
in Brooklyn South last weekend.

06:10.779 --> 06:12.280
Could be a pattern.

06:12.281 --> 06:14.715
Let's canvass the building.
Okay.

06:18.320 --> 06:19.587
Hey, Dad.

06:19.588 --> 06:22.924
We, uh... we might have stumbled
upon something here.

06:27.596 --> 06:29.664
<i>In the massacre last night,</i>

06:29.665 --> 06:31.399
one of the dead
in the ambush

06:31.400 --> 06:33.367
was a confidential
DEA informant.

06:33.368 --> 06:34.669
He was also
in business

06:34.670 --> 06:35.937
with some of
your detectives.

06:35.938 --> 06:37.305
Do you have proof?

06:37.306 --> 06:40.007
Copies of the wire recordings
are being made as we speak.

06:40.008 --> 06:42.510
We have a voice,
but no name to go with it.

06:43.345 --> 06:44.779
Just one?

06:44.780 --> 06:46.347
Just one on tape.

06:46.348 --> 06:49.550
Clearly, this isn't
just a one-man show.

06:49.551 --> 06:51.452
How much money
we talking about?

06:51.453 --> 06:53.154
Given the chatter
leading up to this,

06:53.155 --> 06:56.491
I'd estimate the haul to be
around $12 million in cash,

06:56.492 --> 06:58.526
another 12 in pure heroin.

06:58.527 --> 07:00.995
That's a hell of a pension.

07:00.996 --> 07:03.030
What's the DEA's stance?

07:03.031 --> 07:05.867
We've got almost two years
staked in the operation.

07:05.868 --> 07:08.736
We'd rather not come out of
the shadows for some rogue cops.

07:08.737 --> 07:10.671
We're pulling all our guys out.

07:10.672 --> 07:12.106
Safety Net's
been cleared

07:12.107 --> 07:13.774
for your department
to move ahead.

07:13.775 --> 07:15.877
I appreciate that, Don.

07:17.412 --> 07:18.846
I'm sorry, Commissioner.

07:18.847 --> 07:21.215
I realize this
is the worst kind of news

07:21.216 --> 07:22.984
someone in your position
can get.

07:24.620 --> 07:26.621
No.

07:26.622 --> 07:29.323
But it's a close second.

07:30.926 --> 07:33.060
<i>If you're wearing</i>
<i>gloves, you want</i>

07:33.061 --> 07:35.363
to get to your gun quick,
so you do this--

07:35.364 --> 07:37.365
you reach the gun,
but if you do anything else

07:37.366 --> 07:38.866
with your arm,
the glove drops wherever.

07:38.867 --> 07:40.368
Yeah, so they came
through the window.

07:40.369 --> 07:42.102
Yeah, I'm figuring there
were at least four

07:42.103 --> 07:43.788
if they had to move
that much weight out.

07:43.789 --> 07:45.506
So two through the door
and two through the window.

07:45.507 --> 07:47.441
Right.
You talking to I.A.?

07:47.442 --> 07:48.676
Uh-uh.

07:48.677 --> 07:49.944
Not even Bello?

07:49.945 --> 07:51.045
Why not?

07:51.046 --> 07:52.480
I trust Alex, but he won't know

07:52.481 --> 07:54.515
if the Templar has eyes
and ears over there.

07:54.516 --> 07:56.751
Jamie was there
on a related incident.

07:56.752 --> 07:58.519
I don't want to set off alarms.

07:58.520 --> 08:00.555
But you can't handle this
on your own, Dad.

08:00.556 --> 08:02.823
I'm not going to.
I have you.

08:02.824 --> 08:04.125
And I got Danny.

08:04.126 --> 08:05.526
Can we trust Detective Curatola?

08:05.527 --> 08:06.961
She's solid.

08:06.962 --> 08:08.196
What about me?

08:08.197 --> 08:09.697
I know this is going to be hard

08:09.698 --> 08:12.099
for you, Jamie, but they do
have eyes and ears on you,

08:12.100 --> 08:14.202
so for now, you got to go
about your business

08:14.203 --> 08:16.837
like it's
any other day.

08:16.838 --> 08:18.573
So we have five, six,

08:18.574 --> 08:21.242
and how many men and women
in the NYPD?

08:21.243 --> 08:22.877
We're looking for a few
out of...

08:22.878 --> 08:24.946
35,000, maybe?

08:24.947 --> 08:26.981
Is there anyone else
we can trust?

08:26.982 --> 08:29.350
Yeah, and I will bring them in
at the right time,

08:29.351 --> 08:31.719
but right now,
we don't know how high up

08:31.720 --> 08:33.821
or how deeply this infection
has spread,

08:33.822 --> 08:37.758
so for now,
this operation stays in-house.

08:37.759 --> 08:40.061
In this house.

